description:
Subjects Addressed:
(1) Preventive Medicine in Psalm 91; Exodus 15:26
(2) Before the Coming of Christ, the law of Moses, along with the statutes and judgments are to beremembered and emphasized according to Malachi 4:4 and 5
(3) Prevalence of pestilences indicates that the Second Coming is soon to become a reality
(4) Pestilences defined as diseases according to Deuteronomy 28
(5) Diseases that are affecting the populous today include Ebola, Chikungunya, Enterovirus D68, Marburg, and many more
(6) Many of the diseases now rampant were manufactured in laboratories and unleashed by wicked men, while other diseases are contracted because of individuals ignorance or rejection of Gods statutes, judgments, and laws
(7) We are instructed by God to hearken diligently to His health laws so that we will be free from disease
(8) God instructs His people to follow his original dietary plan found in Genesis1:29 and Genesis 3:18
(9) Although God at one time permitted the use of clean flesh for food, it is no longer safe or condoned by Gods word
(10) A healthy lifestyle will result in a healthy immune system that will work to combat communicable diseases and disease in general
(11) Fasting and praying, showing your total reliance upon God to keep you must be combined with the implementation of the Eight Laws of Health

chapters.title: (8) God instructs His people to follow his original dietary plan found in Genesis1:29 and Genesis
